				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ T_{\text{THz}}(\omega) = \frac{4\tilde{n}}{(1+\tilde{n})^{2}} e^{i(\tilde{n}-1)d\omega/c}, $$\end{document}where, d is the thickness of the GaAs, and ω = 2πν where ν is the frequency. The refractive index was numerically found using the method described in Refs. [20, 30]. Finally, the refractive index was converted to conductivity by Eq. 2, where 𝜖L was replaced by the relative permittivity of GaAs, 𝜖r=ñ2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
